    • lockTag

      public device.sdk.rfid.model.OperationData lockTag(String memMask, String actionMask)
      Execute Lock.

      Parameters:
      memMask - The memory mask specifying the memory regions to lock.

      If the target bank is TID, then memMask = "00030".

      actionMask - The action mask specifying the lock actions for the memory regions

      If actionMask = "00020", you need Access Password when using Read/Write command.

      Please refer the Table 6.50: "Lock Action-field funcitonality" in the EPC Gen2 spec.

      Returns:
      Returns the result. RFIDConst

    • getLinkProfile

      public String getLinkProfile()
      Get the current Link profile value applied to the RFID module.
      Returns:
      Link profile value.

      103: read rate DSB 6.25, 1.5, 640, M1

      302: read rate PR 7.5, 2, 640, M1

      120: read rate DSB 6.25, 1.5, 640, M2

      323: read rate PR 7.5, 2, 640, M2

      345: read rate PR 7.5, 1.5, 640, M4

      344: ET-UB(D) PR 15, 2, 640, M4

      223: ET-LB PR 15, 2, 320, M4

      222: ET-LB PR 20, 2, 320, M2

      241: ET-LB(D) PR 20, 2, 320, M4

      244: FCC(D) PR 20, 2, 250, M4

      285: Sens PR 20, 2, 160, M8

    • setPacketOption

      public int setPacketOption(String newValue)
      Set the Packet option value for the RFID module.

      The option value can be mixed and used in an additive way, such as 11( = 1 + 2 + 8).

      For example, if you want to receive both RSSI and Frequency, set it to 10.

      32 cannot be mixed with other values.

      For example, if you set it to 40(= 8 + 32), you will only receive Frequency.

      It is added to the tag data in the order of RSSI, Frequency, and Checksum.

      R, F, K are added as a prefix in front of the actual value.

      Each item is separated with ";" (semicolon).

      a.g ";RFE8A;F917300;K74"

      Parameters:
      newValue - New value to be applied.

      RFIDConst.PACKET_CHECKSUM

      RFIDConst.PACKET_RSSI

      RFIDConst.PACKET_FREQUENCY

      RFIDConst.PACKET_EPC

      Returns:
      Returns the result. RFIDConst
